{"questionId":"20378","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Two straight fences meet at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> and a field lies between them.</p>\n<p>A horse is tied to a post, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>, by a rope of length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> metres. Point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math> is on one fence and&nbsp;point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>E</mtext></math> is on the other, such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>PD</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>PE</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>PA</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext><mover><mtext>P</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi>θ</mi></math> radians. This is shown in&nbsp;the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f1ba8bcdc1e69afbba140214e41b62dca5c09c35.png\"></p>\n<p>The length of the arc <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>DE</mtext></math> shown in the diagram is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>28</mn><mi>θ</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20378","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ1.8a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down an expression for r in terms of θ.